"{\"uid\": \"kwqc.com-2024-07-12-free-summer-olympics-opening-ceremony-watch-party-families-impacted-by-cancer\", \"text\": \"DAVENPORT, Iowa (KWQC) - Families impacted by cancer are being invited to watch the Summer Olympics opening ceremony.  Cancer Support Community Iowa & NW Illinois at Gilda's Club is hosting an opening ceremony watch party for any families impacted by cancer.  According to a media release, the watch party includes family-friendly competitions, a free lunch, and a livestream of the opening ceremony in Paris.  The event will be at 11:30 a.m. to 1:30 p.m. on July 26 at 1351 W. Central Park Ave., Suite 200, Davenport.  This is an all-ages event, with teens and kids welcome to bring a friend.  Registration for the event is required, and space is limited. For more details and to reserve a spot call 563-326-7504, emailprogram@gildasclub.org, or sign up onlinehere.  Copyright 2024 KWQC. All rights reserved.\"}"